    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The Catalan word trencadís (broken tiles) applies to a kind of mosaic process made up of broken multi-colored ceramic tiles used to cover architectural surfaces. Antoni Gaudí and Josep Maria Jujol made extensive use of this technique.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
